    thinking: "**Analyzing the Requirements**\n\nI\'m currently breaking down the design specifications for \"Kuni,\" focusing on the interactive elements and landing page components. My aim is to define the necessary features based on the visual cues and user\'s intent. Next, I need to outline a basic plan for implementing a web application to match the specs and request.\n\n\n**Defining the Visual Components**\n\nI\'m now diving into the specifics of the landing page design. I\'ve dissected the header/navigation, noting the \"Kuni\" logo, menu items, and CTA button. The hero section is next; I need to figure out how to represent the \"Code & Culture\" theme. A search for a good image is up next. I\'m exploring direct image links for simplicity, but I also have some other layout ideas!\n\n\n**Exploring Image Options**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the image element for the hero section, considering `generate_image`, Unsplash, or a placeholder. My goal is a beautiful, interactive representation that aligns with the \"Code & Culture\" theme. I\'ve got a specific visual in mind: a smiling young Latino student/engineer. I\'m imagining how that image will interact with a text box and buttons!\n\n\n**Clarifying Data Presentation**\n\nI\'m now nailing down the data visualization for the \"Kuni\" landing page. I\'ve got the stats in mind; something big and beautiful. For the image, I\'ll use \"100K+\" Community on TikTok, \"+500\" Students, and a price like \"S/. 30\" (or S/. 30 PE Soles) Accessible Price. The stylized look of the image is going to make it pop!\n\n\n**Outlining Key Features**\n\nI\'m now identifying the key features for the \"Futuros Techies\" section. I\'m focusing on the value proposition: helping people transition into tech from other areas. I\'ve noted the emphasis on actionable tools and personalized guidance in a single session. Next, I am thinking through the components for a clear \"path to success\" section, which will present a simple, step-by-step process with clear calls to action. I am visualizing the use of checklist style components.\n\n\n**Finalizing Landing Page Content**\n\nI\'m now integrating the pricing section, including a compelling \"POR UNICA VEZ\" offer at S/ 30 with key benefits like a 45-minute session and a personalized roadmap. I\'m also including an FAQ section that addresses payment, rescheduling, and group mentoring inquiries. Finally, I\'ve got the footer, featuring the \"Kuni Mentorship\" tagline and essential links for the page.\n\n\n**Adding Interactive Elements**\n\nI\'m now fully committed to making the \"Kuni\" landing page interactive! I\'m planning an interactive booking form with a scheduler, a testimonials viewer, a LinkedIn & CV feedback simulator, and an interactive PDF roadmap builder. I\'m focusing on high fidelity and beautiful styling. I want the page to be an engaging educational experience, which also looks to the skills we could be using: cloudsql-execute-sql, cloudsql-setup, cloudsql-update-schema, firebase-integration, focus-mode, gemini-api (relevant for generating). Finally, I\'ll need to add a privacy policy, terms of service, contact information, and a newsletter sign-up. I\'ll also add a copyright statement.\n\n\n"
